  <span id="freeText10820914554383140659" style="display:none">Putting aside the histhoric context of the tale that is a accesory frame for the picture,the narration, we pass to review.<br /><br />The tale is one of the greatest romantic horror tales,told in first person by a condemned to death by the Toledo Inquisition, with the great prose of Poe.<br />Is a tale about subjetive pass of time,about the subjetive terrorific reality in a sensorial deprived situation,a nightmarish voyage to the unknown next torture, and told in a sort of conscious stream of hopeles fear and terror.<br /><br />Roger Corman directed a interesting movie loosely based in this tale.<br /><br />As only a anecdotic fact, this tale is influenced by the prejudices of Spanish Black Legend.<br />The Inquisition not only murdered people in Spain,we have some examples of others Inquisition murders:<br />Galileo imprisoned in Italy, Juana de Arco murdered in France, Giordano Bruno murdered in Italy, Lucilio Vanini murdered in France, Jan Hus murdered in Germany, Pietro Dabano murdered in Italy, Miguel Servet murdered in Switzerland.<br /><br /></span>
