        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1405588188" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5066869871752580398">Apart from <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/899492.The_Tell_Tale_Heart' title='The Tell-Tale Heart by Edgar Allan Poe' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Tell-Tale Heart</a> that I read for class in junior high; this was the first Poe that I ever really read.....and I was immediately in love! His language was the most beautiful that I had ever come across. I was so entranced by the way he used words that the horrific depiction wasn&apos;t quite coming through as I sat there fascinated with the way he could string words into a sentence like pearls onto a chain. But then, I began to get queazy, forgetting to take a breath....it was a beautifu</span>
  <span id="freeText5066869871752580398" style="display:none">Apart from <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/899492.The_Tell_Tale_Heart" title="The Tell-Tale Heart by Edgar Allan Poe" rel="nofollow noopener">The Tell-Tale Heart</a> that I read for class in junior high; this was the first Poe that I ever really read.....and I was immediately in love! His language was the most beautiful that I had ever come across. I was so entranced by the way he used words that the horrific depiction wasn't quite coming through as I sat there fascinated with the way he could string words into a sentence like pearls onto a chain. But then, I began to get queazy, forgetting to take a breath....it was a beautifully worded truly barbaric tale. The juxtaposition of powerfully poetic language and the horrors hidden inside the prose held me captive. I've never read anyone who can touch him.</span>
