<div id="review_3123201613" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3123201613" />
    <a title="jade" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11030012-jade"><img alt="jade" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1562419355p2/11030012.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3123201613?book_show_action=true">Jan 04, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="jade" class="user" itemprop="url" name="jade" href="/user/show/11030012-jade">jade</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">poe fans, lovers of the creepy, gothic lit aficionados, or all of the above</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to jade by: </span>
      my completed works of poe, gazing gloomily at me from my bookshelf
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11030012-jade?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11030012-jade?shelf=gothic-lit">gothic-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11030012-jade?shelf=horror">horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3123201613" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1117243002026061105"><b>the blurb:</b> <i>this tale of poe&apos;s emphasizes reality over the supernatural.</i><br/><b>me, who just had the most surrealist, hellfire-esque experience of my life:</b> <i>weird flex but ok</i><br/><br/>in all seriousness: this is an <b>interesting</b> one.<br/><br/>poe&apos;s stories often do focus the supernatural, or at least the narrator&apos;s perception of it. this is a balls-to-the-walls (burning metal torture walls, mind you) <b>sentenced-to-death kind of tale</b>, in which a prisoner is tortured by the inquisition.<br/><br/>narrowly escaping his first intended method </span>
  <span id="freeText1117243002026061105" style="display:none"><b>the blurb:</b> <i>this tale of poe's emphasizes reality over the supernatural.</i><br /><b>me, who just had the most surrealist, hellfire-esque experience of my life:</b> <i>weird flex but ok</i><br /><br />in all seriousness: this is an <b>interesting</b> one.<br /><br />poe's stories often do focus the supernatural, or at least the narrator's perception of it. this is a balls-to-the-walls (burning metal torture walls, mind you) <b>sentenced-to-death kind of tale</b>, in which a prisoner is tortured by the inquisition.<br /><br />narrowly escaping his first intended method of death, a pit, they then drug and prep him for another: a swinging blade of a <b>pendulum</b>, slowly descending upon his bound body.<br /><br />this story is all about having <b>your senses overwhelmed</b>; sight, taste, scent, touch. if you're a thriller writer looking for some solid, visceral adjectives and descriptors that'll creep out your audience -- well, you're sure to find them here.<br /><br />wasn't sure if i liked the ending -- i much <b>preferred the surreal</b>, nightmare-like state of what came before. i first thought the whole set-up a metaphor for hell, for torture unending, and thought it'd stay that way.<br /><br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[oh well. thank god he got away! <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />✎ <i>3.5 stars.</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="1117243002026061105" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3123201613">
